1.5 Positioning Statement

NAD does not learn trajectories or densities directly. It learns a stochastic action functional whose stationary paths define a generative distribution. This reframes physics-informed generation from guided sampling to constrained variational inference in path space. The framework is presented as a complete theoretical and algorithmic specification. Exact symplecticity per sample is incompatible with tractable multi-modal generation in chaotic regimes; NAD instead guarantees distributional geometric consistency.

